": "Logging in the test suite uses StringIO, but StringIO has no working `.fileno()`:\r\n\r\n```\r\n(Pdb) stdout.fileno()\r\n*** io.UnsupportedOperation: fileno\u0000\r\n```\r\n\r\nApparently this is known. From cmd.py:\r\n\r\n```\r\n        # TODO: if outputstream is sys.stdout and that one is set to StringIO\r\n        #       we have to \"shim\" it with something providing fileno().\r\n        # This happens when we do not swallow outputs, while allowing nosetest's\r\n        # StringIO to be provided as stdout, crashing the Popen requiring\r\n        # fileno().  In out swallow_outputs, we just use temporary files\r\n        # to overcome this problem.\r\n        # For now necessary test code should be wrapped into swallow_outputs cm\r\n        # to avoid the problem\r\n ```\r\n\r\nI am not clear on why this is NOT a problem on Linux (but happens on Windows all the time).\r\n\r\nSome guidance would be appreciated.\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/2606/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "h